#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:3
msgid "Tax carryover"
msgstr "Pemindahan pajak"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:5
msgid ""
"When performing tax reports, the **tax carryover** feature allows carrying "
"amounts from one period to another without creating new entries."
msgstr ""
"Saat melakukan laporan pajak, fitur **pemindahan pajak** memungkinkan "
"pemindahan jumlah dari satu periode ke periode lain tanpa membuat entri baru."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:8
msgid ""
"It has been created to meet the legal requirements of specific locations, "
"where amounts must be transferred from period to period (for example, "
"because the total of the line is negative)."
msgstr ""
"Fitur ini dibuat untuk memenuhi persyaratan hukum di lokasi tertentu, di "
"mana jumlah harus dipindahkan dari periode ke periode (misalnya, karena "
"total baris bernilai negatif)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:11
msgid ""
"The feature is activated by default in countries where it is required, such "
"as Belgium, France, and Italy. There is no specific configuration required."
msgstr ""
"Fitur ini diaktifkan secara default di negara-negara yang memerlukannya, "
"seperti Belgia, Prancis, dan Italia. Tidak ada konfigurasi khusus yang "
"diperlukan."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:14
msgid ""
"Let’s take an example of a Belgian company that created a credit note of 100 "
"for one of their customers. The due tax is 21%."
msgstr ""
"Mari kita ambil contoh perusahaan Belgia yang membuat nota kredit sebesar "
"100 untuk salah satu pelanggan mereka. Pajak yang harus dibayar adalah 21%."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:None
msgid "Illustration with a credit note"
msgstr "Ilustrasi dengan nota kredit"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:21
msgid ""
"In this case, as per local regulation, grid 81 of the tax report may contain "
"a negative amount. But it must be declared to the government as zero, and "
"the negative amount should be carried over to the next period."
msgstr ""
"Dalam kasus ini, sesuai peraturan lokal, kotak 81 dari laporan pajak dapat "
"berisi jumlah negatif. Namun harus dilaporkan ke pemerintah sebagai nol, dan "
"jumlah negatif harus dipindahkan ke periode berikutnya."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:25
msgid ""
"If we go to :menuselection:`Accounting app --> Reporting --> Tax Report`, a "
"pop-up on line 81 explains that the amount will be carried over in the next "
"period."
msgstr ""
"Jika kita masuk ke :menuselection:`Aplikasi Akuntansi --> Pelaporan --> "
"Laporan Pajak`, sebuah pop-up pada baris 81 menjelaskan bahwa jumlah "
"tersebut akan dipindahkan ke periode berikutnya."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:None
msgid ""
"pop-up message stating the amount will be carried over to the next period"
msgstr ""
"pesan pop-up yang menyatakan jumlah akan dipindahkan ke periode berikutnya"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:32
msgid ""
"At the time of the tax closing period, the tax report shows that the amount "
"was carried over from the previous period. It also indicates the amount that "
"will be carried over to this line in the next period based on the existing "
"transactions and the carryover from the previous period."
msgstr ""
"Pada saat penutupan periode pajak, laporan pajak menunjukkan bahwa jumlah "
"tersebut dipindahkan dari periode sebelumnya. Laporan ini juga menunjukkan "
"jumlah yang akan dipindahkan ke baris ini di periode berikutnya berdasarkan "
"transaksi yang ada dan pemindahan dari periode sebelumnya."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_carryover.rst:None
msgid "Illustration of the tax return"
msgstr "Ilustrasi pengembalian pajak"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_returns.rst:3
msgid "Tax return (VAT report)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_returns.rst:5
msgid ""
"Companies with a registered :abbr:`VAT (Value Added Tax)` number are "
"required to submit a tax return monthly or quarterly, depending on their "
"turnover and the applicable regulatory requirements. A tax return - or VAT "
"report - provides the tax authorities with information about the taxable "
"transactions made by the company. The **output tax** is charged on the sale "
"of goods and services, while the **input tax** refers to the tax included in "
"the price of purchased goods or services. Based on these values, the company "
"can calculate the tax amount they must pay or be refunded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/reporting/tax_returns.rst:13
msgid ""
"`European Commission documentation on VAT <https://ec.europa.eu/"
"taxation_customs/business/vat/what-is-vat_en>`_."
msgstr ""

