#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:3
msgid "B2B (tax excluded) and B2C (tax included) pricing"
msgstr "Harga B2B (tidak termasuk pajak) dan B2C (termasuk pajak)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:5
msgid ""
"When working with consumers, prices are usually expressed with taxes "
"included in the price (e.g., in most eCommerce). But, when you work in a B2B "
"environment, companies usually negotiate prices with taxes excluded."
msgstr ""
"Ketika bekerja dengan konsumen, harga biasanya dinyatakan dengan pajak "
"termasuk dalam harga (misalnya, di sebagian besar eCommerce). Namun, ketika "
"Anda bekerja di lingkungan B2B, perusahaan biasanya menegosiasikan harga "
"tanpa pajak."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:9
msgid ""
"Odoo manages both use cases easily, as long as you register your prices on "
"the product with taxes excluded or included, but not both together. If you "
"manage all your prices with tax included (or excluded) only, you can still "
"easily do sales order with a price having taxes excluded (or included) : "
"that's easy."
msgstr ""
"Odoo mengelola kedua kasus penggunaan dengan mudah, selama Anda mendaftarkan "
"harga Anda pada produk dengan pajak tidak termasuk atau termasuk, tetapi "
"tidak keduanya bersama-sama. Jika Anda mengelola semua harga Anda dengan "
"pajak termasuk (atau tidak termasuk) saja, Anda masih dapat dengan mudah "
"membuat Sales Order dengan harga yang tidak termasuk pajak (atau termasuk): "
"itu mudah."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:14
msgid ""
"This documentation is only for the specific use case where you need to have "
"two references for the price (tax included or excluded), for the same "
"product. The reason of the complexity is that there is not a symmetrical "
"relationship with prices included and prices excluded, as shown in this use "
"case, in Belgium with a tax of 21%:"
msgstr ""
"Dokumentasi ini hanya untuk kasus penggunaan spesifik di mana Anda perlu "
"memiliki dua referensi untuk harga (termasuk pajak atau tidak termasuk), "
"untuk produk yang sama. Alasan kompleksitasnya adalah tidak ada hubungan "
"simetris antara harga termasuk dan harga tidak termasuk, seperti yang "
"ditunjukkan dalam kasus penggunaan ini, di Belgia dengan pajak 21%:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:19
msgid "Your eCommerce has a product at **10€ (taxes included)**"
msgstr "eCommerce Anda memiliki produk seharga **10€ (termasuk pajak)**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:21
msgid "This would do **8.26€ (taxes excluded)** and a **tax of 1.74€**"
msgstr ""
"Ini akan menjadi **8,26€ (tidak termasuk pajak)** dan **pajak sebesar 1,74€**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:23
msgid ""
"But for the same use case, if you register the price without taxes on the "
"product form (8.26€), you get a price with tax included at 9.99€, because:"
msgstr ""
"Namun untuk kasus penggunaan yang sama, jika Anda mencatat harga tanpa pajak "
"pada formulir produk (8,26€), Anda mendapatkan harga dengan pajak termasuk "
"sebesar 9,99€, karena:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:26
msgid "**8.26€ \\* 1.21 = 9.99€**"
msgstr "**8,26€ \\* 1,21 = 9,99€**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:28
msgid ""
"So, depending on how you register your prices on the product form, you will "
"have different results for the price including taxes and the price excluding "
"taxes:"
msgstr ""
"Jadi, tergantung pada bagaimana Anda mencatat harga pada formulir produk, "
"Anda akan mendapatkan hasil yang berbeda untuk harga termasuk pajak dan "
"harga tidak termasuk pajak:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:31
msgid "Taxes Excluded: **8.26€ & 10.00€**"
msgstr "Pajak Tidak Termasuk: **8,26€ & 10,00€**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:33
msgid "Taxes Included: **8.26€ & 9.99€**"
msgstr "Pajak Termasuk: **8,26€ & 9,99€**"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:36
msgid ""
"If you buy 100 pieces at 10€ taxes included, it gets even more tricky. You "
"will get: **1000€ (taxes included) = 826.45€ (price) + 173.55€ (taxes)** "
"Which is very different from a price per piece at 8.26€ tax excluded."
msgstr ""
"Jika Anda membeli 100 buah seharga 10€ dengan pajak termasuk, menjadi lebih "
"rumit. Anda akan mendapatkan: **1000€ (pajak termasuk) = 826,45€ (harga) + "
"173,55€ (pajak)** Yang sangat berbeda dari harga per buah sebesar 8,26€ "
"tanpa pajak."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:40
msgid ""
"This documentation explains how to handle the very specific use case where "
"you need to handle the two prices (tax excluded and included) on the product "
"form within the same company."
msgstr ""
"Dokumentasi ini menjelaskan cara menangani kasus penggunaan yang sangat "
"spesifik di mana Anda perlu menangani dua harga (tidak termasuk dan termasuk "
"pajak) pada formulir produk dalam perusahaan yang sama."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:44
msgid ""
"In terms of finance, you have no more revenues selling your product at 10€ "
"instead of 9.99€ (for a 21% tax), because your revenue will be exactly the "
"same at 9.99€, only the tax is 0.01€ higher. So, if you run an eCommerce in "
"Belgium, make your customer a favor and set your price at 9.99€ instead of "
"10€. Please note that this does not apply to 20€ or 30€, or other tax rates, "
"or a quantity >1. You will also make you a favor since you can manage "
"everything tax excluded, which is less error prone and easier for your "
"salespeople."
msgstr ""
"Dalam hal keuangan, Anda tidak memiliki lebih banyak pendapatan dengan "
"menjual produk Anda seharga 10€ daripada 9,99€ (untuk pajak 21%), karena "
"pendapatan Anda akan sama persis di 9,99€, hanya pajaknya lebih tinggi 0,01"
"€. Jadi, jika Anda menjalankan eCommerce di Belgia, berikan keuntungan "
"kepada pelanggan Anda dan tetapkan harga Anda di 9,99€ daripada 10€. Harap "
"dicatat bahwa ini tidak berlaku untuk 20€ atau 30€, atau tarif pajak "
"lainnya, atau kuantitas >1. Anda juga akan memberikan keuntungan bagi diri "
"Anda sendiri karena Anda dapat mengelola semuanya tanpa pajak, yang lebih "
"sedikit rawan kesalahan dan lebih mudah bagi tenaga penjual Anda."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:55
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/guatemala.rst:12
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/uruguay.rst:12
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Pengantar"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:57
msgid ""
"The best way to avoid this complexity is to choose only one way of managing "
"your prices and stick to it: price without taxes or price with taxes "
"included. Define which one is the default stored on the product form (on the "
"default tax related to the product), and let Odoo compute the other one "
"automatically, based on the pricelist and fiscal position. Negotiate your "
"contracts with customers accordingly. This perfectly works out-of-the-box "
"and you have no specific configuration to do."
msgstr ""
"Cara terbaik untuk menghindari kompleksitas ini adalah dengan memilih hanya "
"satu cara mengelola harga Anda dan konsisten dengannya: harga tanpa pajak "
"atau harga dengan pajak termasuk. Tentukan mana yang menjadi default yang "
"tersimpan pada formulir produk (pada pajak default yang terkait dengan "
"produk), dan biarkan Odoo menghitung yang lain secara otomatis, berdasarkan "
"daftar harga dan posisi fiskal. Negosiasikan kontrak Anda dengan pelanggan "
"sesuai dengan itu. Ini berfungsi dengan sempurna secara langsung dan Anda "
"tidak perlu melakukan konfigurasi khusus."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:63
msgid ""
"If you can not do that and if you really negotiate some prices with tax "
"excluded and, for other customers, others prices with tax included, you must:"
msgstr ""
"Jika Anda tidak dapat melakukan itu dan jika Anda benar-benar menegosiasikan "
"beberapa harga tanpa pajak dan, untuk pelanggan lain, harga lain dengan "
"pajak termasuk, Anda harus:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:66
msgid ""
"always store the default price **tax excluded** on the product form, and "
"apply a tax (price excluded on the product form)"
msgstr ""
"selalu simpan harga default **tanpa pajak** pada formulir produk, dan "
"terapkan pajak (harga tidak termasuk pada formulir produk)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:69
msgid ""
"create a pricelist with prices in **tax included**, for specific customers"
msgstr ""
"buat daftar harga dengan harga **termasuk pajak**, untuk pelanggan tertentu"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:71
msgid ""
"create a fiscal position that switches the tax excluded to a tax included"
msgstr ""
"buat posisi fiskal yang mengalihkan pajak tidak termasuk menjadi pajak "
"termasuk"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:73
msgid ""
"assign both the pricelist and the fiscal position to customers who want to "
"benefit to this pricelist and fiscal position"
msgstr ""
"tetapkan daftar harga dan posisi fiskal kepada pelanggan yang ingin "
"mendapatkan manfaat dari daftar harga dan posisi fiskal ini"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:76
msgid "For the purpose of this documentation, we will use the above use case:"
msgstr ""
"Untuk tujuan dokumentasi ini, kami akan menggunakan kasus penggunaan di atas:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:78
msgid "your product default sale price is 8.26€ tax excluded"
msgstr "harga jual default produk Anda adalah 8,26€ tanpa pajak"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:80
msgid ""
"but we want to sell it at 10€, tax included, in our shops or eCommerce "
"website"
msgstr ""
"tetapi kami ingin menjualnya seharga 10€, termasuk pajak, di toko atau "
"Website eCommerce kami"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:83
msgid "Setting your products"
msgstr "Mengatur produk Anda"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:85
msgid ""
"Your company must be configured with tax excluded by default. This is "
"usually the default configuration, but you can check your **Default Sale "
"Tax** from the menu :menuselection:`Configuration --> Settings` of the "
"Accounting application."
msgstr ""
"Perusahaan Anda harus dikonfigurasi dengan pajak tidak termasuk secara "
"default. Ini biasanya merupakan konfigurasi default, tetapi Anda dapat "
"memeriksa **Pajak Penjualan Default** Anda dari menu "
":menuselection:`Konfigurasi --> Pengaturan` dari aplikasi Akuntansi."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:92
msgid ""
"Once done, you can create a **B2C** pricelist. You can activate the "
"pricelist feature per customer from the menu: :menuselection:`Configuration "
"--> Settings` of the Sale application. Choose the option **different prices "
"per customer segment**."
msgstr ""
"Setelah selesai, Anda dapat membuat daftar harga **B2C**. Anda dapat "
"mengaktifkan fitur daftar harga per pelanggan dari menu: "
":menuselection:`Konfigurasi --> Pengaturan` dari aplikasi Penjualan. Pilih "
"opsi **harga berbeda per segmen pelanggan**."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:96
msgid ""
"Once done, create a B2C pricelist from the "
"menu :menuselection:`Configuration --> Pricelists`. It's also good to rename "
"the default pricelist into B2B to avoid confusion."
msgstr ""
"Setelah selesai, buat daftar harga B2C dari menu "
":menuselection:`Konfigurasi --> Daftar Harga`. Sebaiknya juga ubah nama "
"daftar harga default menjadi B2B untuk menghindari kebingungan."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:99
msgid ""
"Then, create a product at 8.26€, with a tax of 21% (defined as tax not "
"included in price) and set a price on this product for B2C customers at 10€, "
"from the :menuselection:`Sales --> Products` menu of the Sales application:"
msgstr ""
"Kemudian, buat produk seharga 8,26€, dengan pajak 21% (didefinisikan sebagai "
"pajak tidak termasuk dalam harga) dan tetapkan harga produk ini untuk "
"pelanggan B2C sebesar 10€, dari menu :menuselection:`Penjualan --> Produk` "
"di aplikasi Penjualan:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:107
msgid "Setting the B2C fiscal position"
msgstr "Mengatur posisi fiskal B2C"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:109
msgid ""
"From the accounting application, create a B2C fiscal position from this "
"menu: :menuselection:`Configuration --> Fiscal Positions`. This fiscal "
"position should map the VAT 21% (tax excluded of price) with a VAT 21% (tax "
"included in price)"
msgstr ""
"Dari aplikasi akuntansi, buat posisi fiskal B2C dari menu ini: "
":menuselection:`Konfigurasi --> Posisi Fiskal`. Posisi fiskal ini harus "
"memetakan PPN 21% (pajak tidak termasuk harga) dengan PPN 21% (pajak "
"termasuk dalam harga)"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:117
msgid "Test by creating a quotation"
msgstr "Uji dengan membuat penawaran"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:119
msgid ""
"Create a quotation from the Sale application, using "
"the :menuselection:`Sales --> Quotations` menu. You should have the "
"following result: 8.26€ + 1.73€ = 9.99€."
msgstr ""
"Buat penawaran dari aplikasi Sale, menggunakan menu "
":menuselection:`Penjualan --> Penawaran`. Anda seharusnya mendapatkan hasil "
"berikut: 8,26€ + 1,73€ = 9,99€."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:125
msgid ""
"Then, create a quotation but **change the pricelist to B2C and the fiscal "
"position to B2C** on the quotation, before adding your product. You should "
"have the expected result, which is a total price of 10€ for the customer: "
"8.26€ + 1.74€ = 10.00€."
msgstr ""
"Kemudian, buat penawaran tetapi **ubah daftar harga menjadi B2C dan posisi "
"fiskal menjadi B2C** pada penawaran, sebelum menambahkan produk Anda. Anda "
"seharusnya mendapatkan hasil yang diharapkan, yaitu total harga 10€ untuk "
"pelanggan: 8,26€ + 1,74€ = 10,00€."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:132
msgid "This is the expected behavior for a customer of your shop."
msgstr "Ini adalah perilaku yang diharapkan untuk pelanggan toko Anda."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:135
msgid "Avoid changing every sale order"
msgstr "Hindari mengubah setiap sales order"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:137
msgid ""
"If you negotiate a contract with a customer, whether you negotiate tax "
"included or tax excluded, you can set the pricelist and the fiscal position "
"on the customer form so that it will be applied automatically at every sale "
"of this customer."
msgstr ""
"Jika Anda menegosiasikan kontrak dengan pelanggan, baik Anda menegosiasikan "
"termasuk pajak atau tidak termasuk pajak, Anda dapat mengatur daftar harga "
"dan posisi fiskal pada formulir pelanggan sehingga akan diterapkan secara "
"otomatis pada setiap penjualan kepada pelanggan ini."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:141
msgid ""
"The pricelist is in the **Sales & Purchases** tab of the customer form, and "
"the fiscal position is in the accounting tab."
msgstr ""
"Daftar harga berada di tab **Penjualan & Pembelian** pada formulir "
"pelanggan, dan posisi fiskal berada di tab akuntansi."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/B2B_B2C.rst:144
msgid ""
"Note that this is error prone: if you set a fiscal position with tax "
"included in prices but use a pricelist that is not included, you might have "
"wrong prices calculated for you. That's why we usually recommend companies "
"to only work with one price reference."
msgstr ""
"Perhatikan bahwa ini rentan kesalahan: jika Anda mengatur posisi fiskal "
"dengan pajak termasuk dalam harga tetapi menggunakan daftar harga yang tidak "
"termasuk, Anda mungkin mendapatkan harga yang salah. Itulah mengapa kami "
"biasanya merekomendasikan perusahaan untuk hanya bekerja dengan satu "
"referensi harga."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:5
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/brazil.rst:186
msgid "AvaTax integration"
msgstr "Integrasi AvaTax"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:7
msgid ""
"Avalara's *AvaTax* is a cloud-based tax software. Integrating *AvaTax* with "
"Odoo provides real-time and region-specific tax calculations when users "
"sell, purchase, and invoice items in Odoo. *AvaTax* tax calculation is "
"supported with every United Nations charted country, including inter-border "
"transactions."
msgstr ""
"*AvaTax* dari Avalara adalah perangkat lunak pajak berbasis cloud. "
"Mengintegrasikan *AvaTax* dengan Odoo menyediakan perhitungan pajak secara "
"real-time dan spesifik wilayah ketika pengguna menjual, membeli, dan "
"menginvoice item di Odoo. Perhitungan pajak *AvaTax* didukung untuk setiap "
"negara yang terdaftar di Perserikatan Bangsa-Bangsa, termasuk transaksi "
"antar-negara."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:13
msgid ""
"*AvaTax* is only available for integration with databases/companies that "
"have locations in the United States, Canada, and Brazil. This means the "
"fiscal position/country of a database can only be set to the United States, "
"Canada, or Brazil. For more information, reference this "
"documentation: :ref:`accounting/avatax/fiscal_country`."
msgstr ""
"*AvaTax* hanya tersedia untuk integrasi dengan database/perusahaan yang "
"memiliki lokasi di Amerika Serikat, Kanada, dan Brasil. Ini berarti posisi "
"fiskal/negara dari database hanya dapat diatur ke Amerika Serikat, Kanada, "
"atau Brasil. Untuk informasi lebih lanjut, rujuk dokumentasi ini: "
":ref:`accounting/avatax/fiscal_country`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:18
msgid ""
"*AvaTax* accounts for location-based tax rates for each state, county, and "
"city. It improves remittance accuracy by paying close attention to laws, "
"rules, jurisdiction boundaries, and special circumstances (like, tax "
"holidays, and product exemptions). Companies who integrate with *AvaTax* can "
"maintain control of tax-calculations in-house with this simple :abbr:`API "
"(application programming interface)` integration."
msgstr ""
"*AvaTax* memperhitungkan tarif pajak berbasis lokasi untuk setiap negara "
"bagian, county, dan kota. Ini meningkatkan akurasi pengiriman dengan "
"memperhatikan undang-undang, peraturan, batas yurisdiksi, dan keadaan khusus "
"(seperti, hari libur pajak, dan pengecualian produk). Perusahaan yang "
"terintegrasi dengan *AvaTax* dapat mempertahankan kontrol perhitungan pajak "
"secara internal dengan integrasi :abbr:`API (application programming "
"interface)` yang sederhana ini."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:25
msgid "Some limitations exist in Odoo while using AvaTax for tax calculation:"
msgstr ""
"Beberapa keterbatasan ada di Odoo saat menggunakan AvaTax untuk perhitungan "
"pajak:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:27
msgid ""
"AvaTax uses the company address by default. To use the warehouse address, "
"enable :ref:`Allow Ship Later <pos/shop/ship>` in the **POS** app settings."
msgstr ""
"AvaTax menggunakan alamat perusahaan secara default. Untuk menggunakan "
"alamat gudang, aktifkan :ref:`Allow Ship Later <pos/shop/ship>` di "
"pengaturan aplikasi **POS**."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:29
msgid ""
"Excise tax is **not** supported. This includes tobacco/vape taxes, fuel "
"taxes, and other specific industries."
msgstr ""
"Cukai **tidak** didukung. Ini termasuk pajak tembakau/vape, pajak bahan "
"bakar, dan industri spesifik lainnya."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes/avatax.rst:33
msgid ""
"Avalara's support documents: `About AvaTax <https://community.avalara.com/"
"support/s/document-item?language=en_US>`_"
msgstr ""
"Dokumen dukungan Avalara: `About AvaTax <https://community.avalara.com/"
"support/s/document-item?language=en_US>`_"

